.TH MKDEB 1 "2026-05-01" "mkdeb 0.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mkdeb \- package files into a Debian (.deb) package
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mkdeb
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mkdeb
is a small wrapper around
.BR dpkg-deb (1)
that assembles a Debian binary package from a source directory. It can read
package metadata from a
.I .deb.json
or
.I .deb.jsonc
file in the source directory, and copies a pre-staged file hierarchy into
the package root before invoking
.BR dpkg-deb .
.PP
A
.B DEBIAN/control
file is generated from the resolved metadata, a default
.B postinst
script that runs
.BR ldconfig (8)
is installed, and a
.B copyright
file in Debian copyright-format 1.0 is written to
.IR PREFIX/share/doc/PACKAGE/copyright .
.PP
Command-line options take precedence over values read from
.I .deb.json
or
.IR .deb.jsonc .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-name " " \fINAME\fR
Package name. Defaults to the value from
.I .deb.json
or the basename of the source directory. The name is lowercased and
underscores are replaced with hyphens.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version " " \fIVERSION\fR
Package version. Defaults to the value from
.I .deb.json
or
.BR 0.1.0 .
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-description " " \fIDESC\fR
One-line package description.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-maintainer " " \fIEMAIL\fR
Maintainer email. Defaults to
.BR maintainer@example.com .
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-arch " " \fIARCH\fR
Target Debian architecture. Auto-detected from
.BR uname (1)
when omitted (e.g.\&
.B x86_64
maps to
.BR amd64 ,
.B aarch64
to
.BR arm64 ).
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIDIR\fR
Output directory for the resulting
.I .deb
file. Defaults to
.BR ./dist .
Existing
.I *.deb
files in this directory are removed before the build.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-prefix " " \fIPREFIX\fR
Installation prefix used when locating documentation and adjusting
permissions. Defaults to
.BR /usr .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-source " " \fIDIR\fR
Source directory containing
.I .deb.json
/
.I .deb.jsonc
and the pre-staged root hierarchy. Defaults to
.BR . .
.TP
.BR \-\-depends " " \fIDEPS\fR
Comma-separated list of package dependencies, written verbatim into the
.B Depends
control field.
.TP
.BR \-\-section " " \fISECTION\fR
Package section. Defaults to
.BR utils .
.TP
.BR \-\-priority " " \fIPRIORITY\fR
Package priority. Defaults to
.BR optional .
.TP
.BR \-\-homepage " " \fIURL\fR
Project homepage URL, written into the
.B Homepage
control field.
.TP
.BR \-\-license " " \fILICENSE\fR
License identifier, used in the generated
.B copyright
file. Defaults to
.BR MIT .
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print the embedded usage summary and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
If a
.I .deb.jsonc
file is present in the source directory it is preferred over
.IR .deb.json .
.I .deb.jsonc
may contain comments and is preprocessed via
.IR jsonc .
.PP
Recognized keys:
.BR name ", "
.BR version ", "
.BR description ", "
.BR maintainer ", "
.BR arch ", "
.BR depends ", "
.BR section ", "
.BR priority ", "
.BR homepage ", "
.BR license ", "
.BR root .
.PP
The
.B root
key names a directory whose contents are copied into the package root.
For example, with
.B "root"
set to
.I ./pkg-root
and a file at
.IR pkg-root/usr/bin/myapp ,
the resulting package installs
.IR /usr/bin/myapp .
Symbolic links are dereferenced when copying.
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
A minimal layout:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
myapp/
\(em\(em .deb.json
\(em\(em pkg-root/
   \(em\(em usr/bin/myapp
.fi
.RE
.PP
With
.I .deb.json
containing:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
{
  "name": "myapp",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "My app",
  "maintainer": "user@example.com",
  "root": "./pkg-root"
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Build the package:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
mkdeb \-s myapp \-o dist
.fi
.RE
.PP
Override the version on the command line:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
mkdeb \-s myapp \-v 1.0.1 \-\-depends "libc6, libssl3"
.fi
.RE
.SH OUTPUT
The built package is written to
.IR OUTPUT_DIR/NAME_VERSION_ARCH.deb .
After a successful build,
.B mkdeb
prints the output of
.B "dpkg-deb \-\-info"
and
.B "dpkg-deb \-\-contents"
for the produced file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ./.deb.json
Package metadata in JSON.
.TP
.I ./.deb.jsonc
Package metadata in JSON-with-comments. Preferred when both files exist.
.TP
.I ./dist/
Default output directory.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.BR dpkg-deb (1)
must be available on
.IR PATH .
.BR jq (1)
is required when a
.I .deb.json
or
.I .deb.jsonc
file is present.
.I jsonc
is required to parse
.I .deb.jsonc
files.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B mkdeb
exits 0 on success and a non-zero status on any error, including missing
tools, an unreadable source directory, or a failure inside
.BR dpkg-deb .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dpkg-deb (1),
.BR dpkg (1),
.BR jq (1),
.BR ldconfig (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Hamed Ghasemzadeh <hg@evgnomon.org>.
